nl.helixsoft.recordstream

Class Reducer

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.helixsoft.recordstream.AbstractStream<Record>
      • nl.helixsoft.recordstream.AbstractRecordStream
        • nl.helixsoft.recordstream.Reducer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Record>, NextUntilNull<Record>, RecordStream, Stream<Record>

    public class Reducer
extends AbstractRecordStream
    Transforms a RecordStream into another RecordStream by applying an aggregate functions to records that group together.

    Usage examples:

    • Calculate the sum, maximum, or average for each group
    • Flatten a gene annotation map (for example GO annotation). If you start with a gene + GO table, which each row containing only one GO identifier, and a single gene occurring in multiple rows, you can transform this into a table where each gene is in only one row, and the GO annotations are concatenated with a delimiter.

    A Reducer has the following parameters:

    • A parent RecordStream, which will be the input before transformation
    • A grouping column. Two consecutive records are grouped together if they have the same value in the grouping column
    • An accumulator, which is a map of (column, Reducer.GroupFunc) pairs. The GroupFunc is applied to each value of that column in the group, and accumulates the result. Grouping functions can do things like: calculate the min, max, sum or average. Concatenate values with a separator. Or just return the first item.

    I started writing this utility class to work around limitations of the SPARQL GROUP BY implementation of Virtuoso 6. (AVG and SUM cast double to int, CONCAT just takes the first value or complains about maximum row length in temp table, etc...)
